# Reverse proxy with automatic HTTPS (Let's Encrypt) in front of the home server.
#
# Replace the placeholder domain with your own DDNS/domain name pointed at your home's
# public IP, and forward ports 443 (and 80, for the ACME HTTP challenge) from your router
# to this Pi. The app itself only listens on 127.0.0.1:8000 — Caddy is the only thing that
# should ever be reachable directly from the internet.

your-espond-domain.example.com {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
